== Roasted Carrots ==

Adjust racks to top and middle positions and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all produce.

Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{12%oz} on a diagonal into ½-inch-thick pieces. Dice @Yukon Gold potatoes{12%oz} into ½-inch pieces. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens.

Toss carrots on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%tsp}, half the @Fry Seasoning{1%tbsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until golden brown and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

== Scallion Mashed Potatoes ==

Meanwhile, place potatoes in a #medium pot{} with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches. Boil until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Reserve ½ cup potato cooking liquid; drain and return potatoes to pot. Mash with 1 packet @sour cream{6%tbsp} and @butter{1%tbsp} until smooth, adding splashes of reserved potato cooking liquid as needed. Stir in half the scallion greens. Season with salt and pepper.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Crispy Buffalo-Spiced Chicken ==

While potatoes cook, pat @chicken cutlets{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{}; season with salt and pepper.

Place @butter{2%tbsp} in a shallow #microwave-safe dish{}. Microwave until melted, ~{30%seconds}. Stir in @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup}, @Frank's Seasoning Blend{7.2%g}, and a pinch of salt and pepper.

Brush 1 packet sour cream (2 packets for 4 servings) onto tops of chicken in a thin layer. Working one piece at a time, dip brushed sides of chicken into panko mixture, pressing to adhere (no need to coat the undersides).

Place coated sides up on a second lightly oiled baking sheet.

Roast chicken on middle rack until browned and cooked through, ~{15-18%minutes}. Transfer to a #plate{} to rest.

While chicken cooks, in a #small bowl{}, combine @blue cheese dressing{1.5%oz}, scallion whites, and remaining sour cream.

Divide carrots, potatoes, and chicken between plates. Top chicken with blue cheese sauce, remaining scallion greens, and @?hot sauce{1%tsp} if desired. Serve with any remaining blue cheese sauce on the side.